<UserControl xmlns="https://github.com/avaloniaui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
             xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
             xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
             mc:Ignorable="d" d:DesignWidth="800" d:DesignHeight="450"
             x:Class="StellarMVVM_2024.Views.taxes_archive_screen">
	<UserControl.Styles>
		<StyleInclude Source="/Styles/archive info styles/taxes_archive_stylesheet.axaml"/>
	</UserControl.Styles>
	<Panel Background="Pink">
		<StackPanel
			HorizontalAlignment="Center"
			Name="taxesArchiveStackPanel">
			<TextBlock
				Classes="title"
				PointerReleased="returnPrevious">
				taxes
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				1. while tedious, taxes help fund the government and are necessary
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				2. the government also controls the money supply via taxes
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				3. there are three levels of taxes: government, state, and local
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				4. the higher the taxes, the less money supply. the lower the taxes, the more money supply
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				5. tax rates are usually determined on the annual income and household members
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				6. the government can take taxes directly from the paycheck (like paychecks)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				7. companies + local governments also use sales taxes on products to increase their profit/funding
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				8. if a person does not pay their taxes or is of high suspicion, the IRS will investigate them
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				9. another alternative are payday loans (however, interest rates are high in repaying the loan)
			</TextBlock>
			<TextBlock
				Classes="infoText">
				10. people can also meet criteria for tax deductions, reducing tax owed
			</TextBlock>
		</StackPanel>
	</Panel>
</UserControl>
